  <text>
     <body>
     <div type="encomium">
   <head>To my worthy Friend, Master <hi>Edward Filmer,</hi> on his Worke published.</head>
   <l>WHat charming Peales are these,</l>
   <l>That, while they bind the senses, doe so please?</l>
   <l>They are the Mariage-rites</l>
   <l>Of two, the choicest Paire of Mans delights,</l>
   <l>
      <hi>Musique</hi> and <hi>Poesie:</hi>
   </l>
   <l>
      <hi>French</hi> Aire and <hi>English</hi> Verse here Wedded lie.</l>
   <l>Who did this Knot compose,</l>
   <l>Againe hath brought the <hi>Lillie</hi> to the <hi>Rose;</hi>
   </l>
   <l>And, with their Chained dance,</l>
   <l>Recelebrates the ioyfull Match with <hi>France.</hi>
   </l>
   <l>They are a Schoole to win</l>
   <l>The faire <hi>French</hi> Daughter to learne <hi>English</hi> in;</l>
   <l>And, graced with her song,</l>
   <l>To make the Language sweet vpon her tongue.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>Ben: Jonson.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
